BE IT ENACTED BY THE THIRD SENATORIAL DISTRICT DELEGATION PURSUANT TO
CHAPTER 4, DIVISION 1, TITLE 1 OF THE COMMONWEALTH CODE:
1 SECTION 1. PURPOSE.
2 The purpose of this Act is to appropriate local funds from the revenues collected pursuant
3 to Saipan Local Law 22-06.
4 SECTION 2. APPROPRIATION.
5 Notwithstanding any provision(s) of law, statutes, rules, or regulations to the contrary, and
6 pursuant to funds allocated to the Third Senatorial District, the Saipan and Northern Islands
7 Legislative Delegation (SNILD) hereby appropriates $380,000 of the revenues collected pursuant
8 to Saipan Local Law 22-06, as amended, as follows:
9 (A) $200,000.00 to Karidat for its personnel/operations to cover the grant obligations from CJPA
10 that is currently on hold due to the delay of CNMI's single audit; expenditure authority shall

