1 be the Executive Director of Karidat or his/her designee. Provided, however, that should the
2 grant funding for Karidat under CJPA be available, Karidat shall first reimburse the
3 $200,000.00 to the account of the Saipan and Northern Islands Legislative Delegation;
4 (B) $60,000.00 for the Navy Hill Basketball rehabilitation, expenditure authority shall be the
5 Chairperson of the Saipan and Northern Islands Legislative Delegation or his/her designee;
6 (C) $50,000.00 for the CNMI Scholarship and Financial Assistance Office, expenditure authority
7 shall be the Chairperson of the Board or his/her designee;
8 (D) $30,000.00 for the operations of the Saipan and Northern Islands Legislative Delegation,
9 expenditure authority shall be the Chairperson of the Saipan and Northern Islands Legislative
10 Delegation;
11 (E) $20,000.00 for the Carolinian Affairs Office for Cultural Heritage Month and related
12 operational expenses, expenditure authority shall be the Chairperson of the Carolinian
13 Advisory Council or his/her designee; and
14 (F) $20,000.00 for the Indigenous Affairs Office for Cultural Heritage Month and related
15 operational expenses, expenditure authority shall be the Resident Executive of the Indigenous
16 Affairs Office or his/her designee.
17 SECTION 3. REPROGRAMMING.
18 Funds appropriated under this act shall not be reprogrammed for any other purpose.
19 Notwithstanding any other provision of law, all funds appropriated under this Act shall be without
20 fiscal year limitation.
21 SECTION 4. REPORTING OF EXPENDITURES.
22 Those responsible for the expenditure of funds allocated under section 2 of this act shall
23 report all expenses to the Secretary of the Department of Finance by the end of the 2026 calendar
